\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator considered the initial evaluator\'E2\'80\'99s report\'2C the reasons for not accrediting the programme and the representation made by the institution. In terms of the first reason for not accrediting the programme the evaluator is of the opinion that the institution has submitted an adequate response to the initial concerns of the HEQC. It is indicated that the following adaptations have been made to the WIL in response to the concerns raised by the HEQC\'3A\line a\'29 The 10 month internship has been reduced to eight months in which one month is used for campus preparation for the Dissertation. This component is pegged at NQF Level 8 \'2812 credit points\'29\'3B\line b\'29 The introduction period to the WIL has been revised to two months at NQF Level 7 \'2824 credit points\'29 and the remaining 6 months \'2836 credit points\'29 is now at NQF Level 8\'3B \line c\'29 Strategic Management in year three is now pegged at NQF Level 8.\line \line As far as the second reason for not accrediting the programme is concerned\'2C the evaluator stated that no letters of support and intent to support the placement of learners have been included in the institution\'E2\'80\'99s representation. The evaluator\'E2\'80\'99s understanding of the letters of support\'2C or intent to support placements of learners would be issued by organisations undertaking to offer such support. The institution has not provided details of which companies\'E2\'80\'99 \'28or potential industry partners\'E2\'80\'99\'29 agreements are in the process of finalization and the institution has not given details of the companies \'28or potential industry partners\'29 with whom 25 placement opportunities have been secured for purposes of WIL.\line \line The Directorate supports the recommendation that the programme should be provisionally accredited with conditions. \line \line \cell \pard 

